HEADWORD: Enthronization
<hw>En*thron`i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
enthroning; hence, the admission of a bishop to his stall or throne in
his cathedral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

